## Resolved mutable: skill-command-name-source

WebSearch code.claude.com/docs/en/skills: a skill is a directory ~/.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md (personal) or .claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md (project); the DIRECTORY name becomes the slash command; SKILL.md frontmatter requires name+description; add/edit/remove under ~/.claude/skills takes effect within the current session without restart (new top-level dir needs restart). Renaming dir skills/gm-skill->skills/gm yields /gm. No marketplace/npx lib required.